        />

        <section class="answer-block">
          <p>
            <strong>Kanha National Park</strong> is a 940-square-kilometer tiger reserve located in Madhya Pradesh, central India.
            Established as a national park in 1955 and designated a tiger reserve in 1973 under Project Tiger, Kanha is one
            of India's premier wildlife destinations. The park hosts approximately <strong>125 Bengal tigers</strong>,
            Indian leopards, gaur, sloth bears, and the rare hard-ground <strong>Barasingha (swamp deer)</strong> —
            a subspecies saved from extinction at Kanha. Divided into four safari zones (Kanha, Kisli, Mukki, Sarhi) and
            accessed through three gates (Khatia, Mukki, Sarhi), the park remains open from October 1 to June 30 annually.
            Wildmark Resort, located less than 1 km from the main Khatia Gate, serves as a base for safari packages combining
            accommodation, permits, meals, and guided jeep tours.
          </p>
        </section>

        <Backlink       title="Book Kanha Tiger Safari Stay at Khatia Gate"
      description="For the best Kanha tiger safari packages near Khatia Gate — including AC accommodation, all meals, forest permits, and guided jeep tours — check Kanha Safari Stay at Wildmark Resort."
